Define _XOPEN_SOURCE=500 to permit headers to prototype strdup() with -std=99

../mesa/program/symbol_table.c: In function ‘_mesa_symbol_table_add_symbol’:
../mesa/program/symbol_table.c:341:8: warning: implicit declaration of function ‘strdup’ [-Wimplicit-function-declaration]
        hdr->name = strdup(name);
        ^
../mesa/program/symbol_table.c:341:18: warning: assignment makes pointer from integer without a cast [enabled by default]
        hdr->name = strdup(name);
                  ^
../mesa/program/symbol_table.c: In function ‘_mesa_symbol_table_add_global_symbol’:
../mesa/program/symbol_table.c:398:19: warning: assignment makes pointer from integer without a cast [enabled by default]
         hdr->name = strdup(name);

If we fail to do this, the implicit int return of strdup() being converted to a char * causes builtin_compiler to fail to
function correctly on 64-bit cygwin...

